The paper also involves the use of one-dimensional convolutional layers, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks, suggesting that it could also belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). 

Furthermore, the paper involves training and comparing different models, which could fall under the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.SD (Software Engineering). 

The paper also involves the evaluation of model performance, which could fall under the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

Finally, the paper involves the exploration of different neural network architectures, which could fall under the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
